Here is an example. The model for boire, 2-17, has the following alteration:

r1p, r2p, b1p, b2p: 2, 2, UV

This alteration results in the following conjugations:

nous $bUVons$ (~not~ boions)
vous $bUVez$ (~not~ boiez)
nous $bUVions$ (~not~ boiions)
vous $bUViez$ (~not~ boiiez)

~Conjuguer~ colors capital letters in alterations red, signifying irregularity.

An asterisk at the end of letters to swap in means an unpredictable ending. For example, the model for valoir, 4-5A, has the following alteration:

