h2s, h1p, h2p: three person-numbers of the impÃ©ratif

The person-number ~A~ means â€œall sixâ€. For example, xA is equivalent to x1s, x2s, x3s, x1p, x2p, x3p. Likewise, rA is equivalent to r1s, r2s, r3s, r1p, r2p, r3p.

